    73	DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
    74	DB_PORT=3306
    75	DB_USER=gallery
    76	DB_PASSWORD=password
    77	DB_NAME=gallery
    78	ADMIN_PASSWORD=<strong-16+-char-secret-or-argon2-hash>
    79	SESSION_SECRET=<random-64-char-hex>
    80	```
    81	
    82	## Key Files & Patterns
    83	
    84	| File | Purpose |
    85	|------|---------|
    86	| `apps/web/src/app/actions.ts` | Server actions for uploads, image CRUD, auth, session management |
    87	| `apps/web/src/db/schema.ts` | Drizzle ORM schema with composite indexes |
    88	| `apps/web/src/lib/process-image.ts` | Sharp pipeline (parallel AVIF/WebP/JPEG, ICC parsing, bounds checks) |
    89	| `apps/web/src/lib/data.ts` | Data access layer with React cache() deduplication |
    90	| `apps/web/src/proxy.ts` | i18n routing + middleware-level admin auth guard |
    91	| `apps/web/src/app/[locale]/admin/db-actions.ts` | DB backup/restore with security hardening |
    92	| `apps/web/src/app/api/admin/db/download/route.ts` | Authenticated backup file download |
    93	| `apps/web/src/site-config.json` | Site metadata (title, SEO, links) |
    94	
    95	- **Storage Backend (Not Yet Integrated):** The `@/lib/storage` module still exists as an internal abstraction, but the product currently supports local filesystem storage only. Do not document or expose S3/MinIO switching as a supported admin feature until the upload/processing/serving pipeline is wired end-to-end.
    96	
    97	## Database Schema (Key Tables)
    98	
    99	- `images` - Photo metadata, EXIF data, filenames
   100	- `topics` - Photo albums/categories
   101	- `tags` / `imageTags` - Tagging system
   102	- `adminUsers` / `sessions` - Multi-user authentication
   103	- `sharedGroups` / `sharedGroupImages` - Public sharing
   104	
   105	## Image Upload Flow
   106	
   107	1. Files uploaded via `uploadImages()` server action
   108	2. Original saved to the private upload store under `data/uploads/original/`
   109	3. Sharp processes to AVIF/WebP/JPEG (async queue)
   110	4. EXIF extracted and stored in database
   111	5. Processed files in `public/uploads/{avif,webp,jpeg}/`
   112	
   113	## Security Architecture
   114	
   115	### Authentication & Sessions
   116	- Passwords hashed with **Argon2** (industry-standard memory-hard KDF)
   117	- Session tokens: HMAC-SHA256 signed, verified with `timingSafeEqual` (constant-time)
   118	- Cookie attributes: `httpOnly`, `secure` (in production), `sameSite: lax`, `path: /`
   119	- Session secret: `SESSION_SECRET` env var is required in production; dev/test can fall back to a DB-stored generated secret in `admin_settings`
   120	- Expired sessions purged automatically (hourly background job)
   121	- Login rate limiting: 5 attempts per 15-minute window per IP, with bounded Map + LRU eviction
   122	
   123	### Middleware Auth Guard
   124	- `proxy.ts` checks `admin_session` cookie for all `/[locale]/admin/*` sub-routes
   125	- Unauthenticated requests redirected to login page
   126	- Every server action independently verifies auth via `isAdmin()` (defense in depth)
   127	- Last admin deletion prevented to avoid lockout
   128	
   129	### File Upload Security
   130	- **Path traversal prevention**: `SAFE_SEGMENT` regex + `ALLOWED_UPLOAD_DIRS` whitelist + `resolvedPath.startsWith()` containment
   131	- **Symlink rejection**: Both upload routes use `lstat()` and reject `isSymbolicLink()`
   132	- **Filename sanitization**: UUIDs via `crypto.randomUUID()` (no user-controlled filenames on disk)
   133	- **Decompression bomb mitigation**: Sharp `limitInputPixels` configured
   134	- **Directory whitelist**: Only `jpeg`, `webp`, `avif` served publicly; `original/` excluded
   135	- **Headers**: `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, immutable cache-control
   136	
   137	### Database Security
   138	- All queries via Drizzle ORM (parameterized, no raw SQL with user input)
   139	- LIKE wildcards (`%`, `_`, `\`) escaped in search to prevent wildcard abuse
   140	- DB backup dumps stored in `data/backups/` (non-public), served via authenticated API route
   141	- DB restore validates file headers and uses `--one-database` flag
   142	- CSV export escapes formula injection characters (`=`, `+`, `-`, `@`, `\t`, `\r`)
   143	- `MYSQL_PWD` env var used for mysqldump/restore (not `-p` flag)
   144	
   145	### Privacy
   146	- GPS coordinates (`latitude`, `longitude`) excluded from public API responses
   147	- `filename_original` and `user_filename` excluded from public queries
   148	- `adminSelectFields` includes all fields (including PII) for authenticated admin routes
   149	- `publicSelectFields` derived from `adminSelectFields` by omitting PII fields — separate object reference prevents accidental leakage
   150	- Compile-time guard (`_SensitiveKeysInPublic`) enforces no sensitive keys in `publicSelectFields`
   151	
   152	## Database Indexes
   153	
   154	The `images` table has composite indexes optimized for query patterns:
   155	- `(processed, capture_date, created_at)` — homepage and gallery listing sort
   156	- `(processed, created_at)` — prev/next navigation
   157	- `(topic, processed, capture_date, created_at)` — topic-filtered listings
   158	- `(user_filename)` — upload deduplication
   159	- `image_tags(tag_id)` — tag JOIN performance
   160	
   161	Connection pool: 10 connections, queue limit 20, keepalive enabled.
   162	
   163	## Image Processing Pipeline
   164	
   165	1. Files uploaded via `uploadImages()` server action
   166	2. Original saved to the private upload store under `data/uploads/original/`
   167	3. Enqueued to `PQueue` (concurrency: 1) for background processing
   168	4. Queue job **claims** image (conditional `WHERE processed = false`) before processing
   169	5. Sharp processes to **AVIF/WebP/JPEG in parallel** (`Promise.all`) at 4 sizes each
   170	6. Single Sharp instance with `clone()` (avoids triple buffer decode)
   171	7. Conditional UPDATE marks as processed; if image was deleted mid-processing, orphaned files are cleaned up
   172	8. EXIF extracted with **bounds-checked ICC profile parsing** (capped tagCount, string lengths)
   173	9. Blur placeholder generated at 16px for instant loading
   174	
   175	## Race Condition Protections
   176	
   177	- **Delete-while-processing**: Queue checks row exists before + conditional UPDATE after processing; orphaned files cleaned up
   178	- **Concurrent tag creation**: `INSERT IGNORE` + slug collision detection with warnings
   179	- **Topic slug rename**: Transaction wraps reference updates before PK rename
   180	- **Batch delete**: Wrapped in DB transaction (imageTags + images atomic)
   181	- **Single delete**: Also transactional, removes ID from enqueued set
   182	- **`createTopic` TOCTOU**: Catches `ER_DUP_ENTRY` instead of check-then-insert
   183	- **`ensureDirs`**: Promise-based singleton prevents concurrent mkdir
   184	- **Session secret init**: `INSERT IGNORE` + re-fetch pattern for multi-process safety
   185	
   186	## Performance Optimizations
   187	
   188	- **React `cache()`** wraps `getImage`, `getTopicBySlug`, `getTopicsWithAliases` for SSR deduplication
   189	- **`Promise.all`** parallelizes independent DB queries in `getImage()` (tags + prev + next)
   190	- **ISR caching**: Photo pages (1 week), topic/home pages (1 hour), admin pages force-dynamic
   191	- **Masonry grid**: `useMemo` for reorder, `requestAnimationFrame` debounced resize
   192	- **ImageZoom**: Ref-based DOM manipulation (no React re-renders on mousemove)
   193	- **Histogram**: Canvas capped at 256x256 for fast computation
   194	
   195	## Permanently Deferred
   196	- **2FA/WebAuthn**: Not planned. Single-user admin with Argon2id + rate limiting is sufficient for a personal gallery. Adding TOTP/WebAuthn would add complexity without proportional benefit.
   197	
   198	## Important Notes
   199	
   200	- **Node.js 24+** required, **TypeScript 6.0+**
   201	- Processed images are stored in `apps/web/public/uploads/`; original uploads are stored privately under the data volume — **ensure both are persisted in Docker**
   202	- Max upload size: 200MB per file, 2 GiB total per batch by default, 100 files max (configurable via `UPLOAD_MAX_TOTAL_BYTES`)
   203	- Uses `output: 'standalone'` for Docker deployments
   204	- DB backups stored in `data/backups/` (volume-mounted, not public)
   205	
   206	## Git Workflow (from AGENTS.md)
   207	
   208	- Always commit and push all changes
   209	- Use gitmoji in commit messages (e.g., ✨ :sparkles:, 🐛 :bug:, 📝 :memo:)
   210	
   211	## Testing
   212	
   213	The repository has a formal test surface:
   214	
   215	- `npm test --workspace=apps/web` — Vitest unit tests in `apps/web/src/__tests__/`
   216	- `npm run test:e2e --workspace=apps/web` — Playwright end-to-end tests in `apps/web/e2e/`
   217	- `npm run lint --workspace=apps/web` — ESLint
   218	
   219	## Deployment Checklist
   220	

