     1	# GalleryKit — Web Application
     2	
     3	The main Next.js application for GalleryKit.
     4	
     5	See the [root README](../../README.md) for full documentation.
     6	
     7	## Quick Start
     8	
     9	```bash
    10	npm install
    11	npm run dev
    12	```
    13	
    14	## Scripts
    15	
    16	| Command | Description |
    17	|---------|------------|
    18	| `npm run dev` | Start development server |
    19	| `npm run build` | Production build |
    20	| `npm run lint` | ESLint check |
    21	| `npm run db:push` | Push schema to MySQL |
    22	| `npm run db:seed` | Seed admin user |
    23	| `npm run init` | Apply committed migrations, then seed admin |
    24	
    25	## Environment notes
    26	
    27	- `BASE_URL` should point at the public app origin used for sitemap/metadata URLs.
    28	- `IMAGE_BASE_URL` is optional. Set it to an absolute CDN origin or path prefix (for example `https://cdn.example.com` or `https://cdn.example.com/gallery`) **before** `next build` so Next.js and CSP both allow the remote asset host.
    29	- Leave `IMAGE_BASE_URL` unset for local/self-hosted uploads served directly from the app.
    30	- Total batch upload size defaults to **2 GiB**. Override with `UPLOAD_MAX_TOTAL_BYTES` only if your deployment can safely absorb larger multipart bodies.
    31	- Set `TRUST_PROXY=true` when running behind the provided nginx reverse proxy or another trusted proxy chain so rate limits use real client IPs.
    32	- The checked-in `docker-compose.yml` assumes a Linux host with `network_mode: host`, a host-managed MySQL instance, and a host-side `src/site-config.json` bind mount.
    33	- If `ADMIN_PASSWORD` is stored as an Argon2 hash, set a separate plaintext `E2E_ADMIN_PASSWORD` for opt-in Playwright admin login flows.
    34	- Remote admin Playwright runs are blocked by default; set `E2E_ALLOW_REMOTE_ADMIN=true` only when you intentionally want to exercise a non-local target with a dedicated `E2E_ADMIN_PASSWORD`.

